---
import ToolLayout from '../../layouts/ToolLayout.astro';

const faqs = [
  {
    question: "How long should a podcast intro script be?",
    answer: "The ideal podcast intro length is between 15 and 45 seconds (approx. 40 to 100 words). Listeners judge audio quality within the first 30 seconds, so keeping your hook brief and engaging is essential for high audience retention."
  },
  {
    question: "What should be included in a professional podcast intro?",
    answer: "A complete podcast intro includes your show title, host name, a quick teaser hook of the episode topic or guest name, background intro music cues, and a brief call-to-action (CTA) to subscribe or follow."
  },
  {
    question: "What are music directions in a podcast intro script?",
    answer: "Music directions (like [Upbeat Intro Music Fades In] or [Music Fades Out]) indicate where audio cues, sound effects, or background beats should enter and fade out during voiceover recording or editing."
  },
  {
    question: "Should I record a fresh intro for every episode?",
    answer: "Many podcasters use a hybrid approach: a consistent 10-second channel intro audio track followed by a freshly recorded 20-second episode teaser that highlights the specific topic or guest of the day."
  },
  {
    question: "Can I use this tool to write podcast outros?",
    answer: "Yes, you can adapt these intro scripts into podcast outro scripts by toggling the subscribe and review call-to-action (CTA) settings."
  }
];
---

<ToolLayout
  title="Podcast Intro Generator - Catchy Audio Hook Scripts"
  description="Generate engaging, high-retention podcast intro scripts and audio voiceover hooks. Customize scripts with music directions and sponsor placeholders."
  toolName="Podcast Intro Generator"
  toolDescription="Create unique podcast intro scripts with sound cues. Customize tone, add episode hooks, and preview live teleprompter voiceover cards."
  category="Writing Tools"
  faqs={faqs}
>
  <div slot="calculator" class="calc-card glass">
    <!-- Main Advanced Grid Layout -->
    <div class="calc-grid">
      <!-- Left Column: Generator Inputs -->
      <div class="calc-form-column">
        <div class="calc-form">
          <!-- Show Name Input -->
          <div class="form-group">
            <label for="show-name-input" class="icon-label">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="1.5" stroke="currentColor" class="field-icon">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M12 18.75a6 6 0 0 0 6-6v-1.5m-6 7.5a6 6 0 0 1-6-6v-1.5m6 7.5v3.75m-3.75 0h7.5M12 15.75a3 3 0 0 1-3-3V4.5a3 3 0 1 1 6 0v8.25a3 3 0 0 1-3 3Z" />
              </svg>
              Podcast Show Name
            </label>
            <input type="text" id="show-name-input" class="form-input" placeholder="e.g. The Tech Chronicles, Mindset Uncut" value="The Tech Chronicles" />
          </div>

          <!-- Host Name Input -->
          <div class="form-group">
            <label for="host-name-input" class="icon-label">Host Name(s)</label>
            <input type="text" id="host-name-input" class="form-input" placeholder="e.g. Alex & Sarah, Creators Feel" value="Alex & Sarah" />
          </div>

          <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); gap: 1rem;">
            <!-- Topic / Guest Input -->
            <div class="form-group">
              <label for="topic-input" class="icon-label">Episode Topic / Guest</label>
              <input type="text" id="topic-input" class="form-input" style="height: 48px;" placeholder="e.g. AI tools with John Doe" value="building SaaS with John Doe" />
            </div>

            <!-- Intro Style Select -->
            <div class="form-group">
              <label for="style-select" class="icon-label">Intro Style</label>
              <select id="style-select" class="form-input" style="height: 48px; background: var(--color-bg); border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: var(--radius-md); padding: 0 12px; color: var(--color-text);">
                <option value="punchy">High-Energy & Punchy (15-30s)</option>
                <option value="conversational">Conversational & Friendly (30-45s)</option>
                <option value="teaser">Storytelling Teaser Hook (45-60s)</option>
                <option value="corporate">Professional & Corporate (30-45s)</option>
              </select>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Formatting Checkboxes -->
          <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.75rem; background: var(--color-bg-alt); padding: 0.75rem 1rem; border-radius: 12px; border: 1px solid var(--color-border);">
            <span style="font-size: 0.72rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--color-text-muted); text-transform: uppercase;">Voiceover Cues & Options</span>
            
            <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.5rem; font-size: 0.88rem;">
              <label style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.5rem; cursor: pointer; color: var(--color-text);">
                <input type="checkbox" id="music-check" checked style="accent-color: var(--color-brand); width: 16px; height: 16px;" />
                Include Music / Sound Cue Directions (e.g. [Music Fades In])
              </label>
              <label style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.5rem; cursor: pointer; color: var(--color-text);">
                <input type="checkbox" id="sponsor-check" style="accent-color: var(--color-brand); width: 16px; height: 16px;" />
                Include Sponsor Shoutout Placeholder
              </label>
              <label style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.5rem; cursor: pointer; color: var(--color-text);">
                <input type="checkbox" id="cta-check" checked style="accent-color: var(--color-brand); width: 16px; height: 16px;" />
                Include Subscribe Call to Action (CTA)
              </label>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Actions -->
          <div class="form-actions">
            <button type="button" id="generate-btn" class="calc-btn">Generate Intros</button>
            <button type="button" id="reset-btn" class="calc-btn-secondary">Reset Inputs</button>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Right Column: Live Mockup Card -->
      <div class="calc-editor-column">
        <!-- Live Teleprompter Studio Voiceover Script Mockup -->
        <div class="podcast-teleprompter-card glass" style="background: #0f172a; color: #ffffff; border-radius: 16px; overflow: hidden; max-width: 320px; margin: 0 auto; width: 100%; border: 1px solid #1e293b; text-align: left; box-shadow: var(--shadow-md); font-family: var(--font-body); padding: 1.25rem;">
          <!-- Top Studio Header Bar -->
          <div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; border-bottom: 1px solid #1e293b; padding-bottom: 0.5rem;">
            <span style="font-size: 0.7rem; font-weight: 800; color: #38bdf8; text-transform: uppercase; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 6px;">
              <span style="width: 8px; height: 8px; border-radius: 50%; background: #ef4444; display: inline-block;"></span> Studio Teleprompter
            </span>
            <span style="font-size: 0.68rem; color: #94a3b8;">Est. 25-30s</span>
          </div>

          <!-- Voiceover Script Header -->
          <span id="mockup-show-header" style="font-size: 0.8rem; font-weight: 700; color: #a855f7; display: block; margin-bottom: 6px;">
            The Tech Chronicles • Hosted by Alex & Sarah
          </span>

          <!-- Script Body Text updating live -->
          <div id="mockup-script-body" style="font-size: 0.8rem; color: #f1f5f9; line-height: 1.5; max-height: 160px; overflow-y: auto; padding-right: 4px; font-family: var(--font-body);">
            [Upbeat Intro Music Fades In]<br /><br />
            Welcome back to The Tech Chronicles! I am Alex & Sarah, and today we are diving deep into building SaaS with John Doe. Make sure to hit subscribe before we jump in!
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Generated Results Section -->
    <div id="results-wrapper" class="hidden" style="margin-top: 2rem; border-top: 1px dashed var(--color-border); padding-top: 1.5rem;">
      <h3 style="font-size: 1.05rem; font-weight: 800; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--color-text); margin: 0 0 1rem 0; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.5rem;">
        <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="1.5" stroke="currentColor" style="width: 20px; height: 20px; color: var(--color-brand);">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M9 12.75 11.25 15 15 9.75M21 12c0 1.268-.63 2.39-1.593 3.068a3.745 3.745 0 0 1-1.043 3.296 3.745 3.745 0 0 1-3.296 1.043A3.745 3.745 0 0 1 12 21c-1.268 0-2.39-.63-3.068-1.593a3.746 3.746 0 0 1-3.296-1.043 3.745 3.745 0 0 1-1.043-3.296A3.745 3.745 0 0 1 3 12c0-1.268.63-2.39 1.593-3.068a3.745 3.745 0 0 1 1.043-3.296 3.746 3.746 0 0 1 3.296-1.043A3.746 3.746 0 0 1 12 3c1.268 0 2.39.63 3.068 1.593a3.746 3.746 0 0 1 3.296 1.043 3.746 3.746 0 0 1 1.043 3.296A3.745 3.745 0 0 1 21 12Z" />
        </svg>
        Suggested Podcast Intro Scripts
      </h3>

      <div class="usernames-grid" id="generated-intros-container">
        <!-- Results dynamic content goes here -->
      </div>

      <div style="display: flex; justify-content: center; margin-top: 1.5rem;">
        <button type="button" id="generate-more-btn" class="calc-btn" style="max-width: 200px; padding: 0 1.5rem;">Generate More</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div slot="about" class="editorial-content">
    <h2>Podcast Intro Generator: Write High-Retention Voiceover Scripts</h2>
    <div style="margin: 1.5rem 0; background: var(--color-bg-alt); padding: 1.25rem; border-radius: var(--radius-md); border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-left: 4px solid var(--color-brand);">
      <p style="margin: 0; font-weight: 600; font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.5;">
        📝 <strong>Looking for optimized episode show notes?</strong> Use our free <a href="/tools/podcast-description-generator" style="color: var(--color-brand); text-decoration: underline;">Podcast Description Generator</a> to craft search-compliant episode summaries for Spotify and Apple Podcasts.
      </p>
    </div>

    <h3>Introduction</h3>
    <p>
      In audio podcasting, your episode intro is your single chance to hook a new listener before they drop off. Studies show that audio listeners judge episode production value within the first 30 seconds. If your voiceover intro is rambly, quiet, or unfocused, listeners will tap the back button. Writing a punchy, well-structured script ensures you hook your audience instantly, communicate episode value, and direct listeners to subscribe. Our free <strong>podcast intro generator</strong> creates professional intro scripts with sound cues and call-to-action placeholders automatically.
    </p>

    <h3>How to Use This Tool</h3>
    <p>
      To craft and audit custom podcast intro scripts in real-time, follow these simple directions:
    </p>
    <ol>
      <li><strong>Podcast Show Name:</strong> Enter your show or channel name.</li>
      <li><strong>Host Name(s):</strong> Enter your host or co-host name(s).</li>
      <li><strong>Episode Topic / Guest:</strong> Enter the specific episode focus or guest name.</li>
      <li><strong>Intro Style:</strong> Select an intro voice (Punchy, Conversational, Storytelling Teaser, or Corporate).</li>
      <li><strong>Voiceover Options:</strong> Select toggles for music directions, sponsor placeholders, or subscribe CTAs.</li>
      <li><strong>Generate List:</strong> Click <strong>Generate Intros</strong> to view 15 custom options.</li>
      <li><strong>Preview & Copy:</strong> Click any script card to preview it inside the teleprompter studio mockup, and copy it instantly. Click <strong>Generate More</strong> to append 5 more options.</li>
    </ol>

    <h3>What is Podcast Intro</h3>
    <p>
      A <strong>podcast intro</strong> is the opening audio segment of a podcast episode that welcomes listeners, introduces the hosts, and hooks the audience with the main episode topic or guest highlight. Writing great <strong>podcast intro scripts</strong> involves balancing your brand's core show name with an engaging episode-specific teaser. Before recording your voiceover track, ensure your show title is short and brandable using our <a href="/tools/podcast-name-generator">Podcast Name Generator</a>. Most professional audio intros range between 15 and 45 seconds in length.
    </p>

    <h3>How Does It Work?</h3>
    <p>
      The generator processes your episode details through proven broadcasting frameworks:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Hook Scripting:</strong> Combines host authority with immediate topic teasers to maximize listener retention.</li>
      <li><strong>Audio Direction Cues:</strong> Inserts standardized production cues (like `[Upbeat Intro Music Fades In]`) for your audio editor.</li>
      <li><strong>Action Triggers:</strong> Seamlessly weaves in subscription reminders and sponsor shoutouts. You can also generate dedicated calls-to-action using our <a href="/tools/cta-generator">CTA Generator</a>.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>How To Use</h3>
    <p>
      Using our generator is easy. Simply fill out your show title, host names, and episode topic, select your preferred intro style, and click generate. Clicking any script updates the live teleprompter mockup, letting you read through the voiceover script before copying it for your recording session.
    </p>

    <h3>Who Should Use This Tool?</h3>
    <p>
      This generator is designed for:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Solo Podcasters:</strong> Creating quick, professional intro scripts for weekly episodes.</li>
      <li><strong>Co-Host Duos:</strong> Structuring joint intro dialogues and conversational hooks.</li>
      <li><strong>Voiceover Artists & Producers:</strong> Writing client intro scripts with embedded sound effect cues.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</ToolLayout>

